    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "this error occurs because the `CustomError` is no longer defined in the scope of the contract, but you are trying to access it as such. \r\nif you are importing the file with the directive in a form of `import \"some-path.sol\"`, it imports all global symbols (like `MyContract` & `CustomError`) into the current scope. the solution is to call `vm.expectRevert(CustomError.selector);`",
